Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt:
11:09 AM/ RM 203. Defendant Cory H. Hansen appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Elizabeth Gebert in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court reviews case history. Case was to be called on 10/24, but was rescheduled for today as Court was overbooked. Court notes status of counsel report. Def. continues to wish for counsel. Court notes Def. has waived time limits for P.H. State has complied with victims rights.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

2:59 PM/ RM 301. Defendant Cory H. Hansen appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court reviews case history and appointment of counsel report. Def. continues to ask for counsel. Court will find good cause to go past time limits for P.H. if Def. wishes to waive time limits and questions if Def. would like to waive time limits. Def. would like to waive time limits and wait for counsel. Court accepts waiver of time limits. Bond continues.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 24, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

3:21 PM Defendant Cory H. Hansen appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Prosecuting attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert in court for the State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court reviews PD status of counsel. Def. continues to ask for counsel. Court agrees Def. should have counsel and finds good cause to go past time limits. State has complied with victim rights.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

4:21 PM Defendant Cory H. Hansen appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties. Def. given Atty rights and given 4 options, PD, hire own or court appointed Atty or represent self. Def. wishes to attain counsel and has been in contact with PD Office. Def. continues to wish for counsel and court finds good cause to go past time limits. State makes remarks and is in compliance with victim rights. Bond continues.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Memorandum of Law in Support of Defendant's Motion
Routed to JA

to Compel the State to file a criminal complaint or release Cory Hansen from Monetary Conditions of Bond
Routed to JA

Maintain Absolute Sobriety. 
No illegal use or possession of controlled substances.
No driving a motor vehicle,  
No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license. 
No contact with immediately family of deceased victim,. 
Not to leave State of Wisconsin.
Surrender passport to Langlade County Sheriff Dept.

1:15 PM Defendant Cory H Hansen appeared by video, via zoom.  State of Wisconsin Kelly Hays appears in court. No complaint filed yet. Bond hearing and riverside hearing set for today.  Possible charges and probable cause given by State, Hit & Run resulting in death, repeater, Homicide by intoxication of vehicle, repeater, & Theft to Law enforcement Officer, repeater. State request cash bond, Maintain Absolute Sobriety. No illegal use or possession of controlled substances, No driving a motor vehicle,  No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license. No contact with immediately family of deceased victim,   Not to leave State of WI and Surrender passport to Langlade County Sheriff Dept. Def. is homeless. Def. has noting RE: Bond.  Court orders $500,000.00 cash bond with conditions.  State has complied with victim rights. Def. given attorney rights.  Court is finding probable cause. Def. advised bond may be addressed at later date. Court adjourns @ 1:29 pm.
Hearing scheduled for September 12, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
